Someone who is a nascent entrepreneur has the motivation and ability to launch a company but hasn't done anything to get the ball rolling. In the same way as nascent entrepreneurs have the capacity and desire to launch a new enterprise inside an existing firm, nascent intrapreneurs have these qualities but have not yet made any concrete efforts to do so. People who are "latent entrepreneurs" are those who want to be their own boss and have the ability to do so, but haven't yet found a viable company idea or made any concrete measures toward making their dream a reality. There are three distinct categories of aspiring entrepreneurs, each of whom is capable of launching a new firm or endeavor, but at different points in the process. 